[1] Clarification
Date: 29 Apr 2010
From: Sona Bari <baris@who.int> [edited]


I wish to refer to [the report from ProMED-RUS
in] your posting [Poliomyelitis - Worldwide (04):
Tajikistan, Uzbekistan susp 20100424.1319] in
which it is stated, in the context of the polio
outbreak in Tajikistan, that "Cases have also
been detected in Uzbekistan and Afghanistan."

Please allow me to clarify that no cases of polio
have been confirmed in Uzbekistan to date and
that polio cases reported this year [2010] in
Afghanistan (10 to date) are not related to the
outbreak in Tajikistan. No cases have been
detected in the areas of Afghanistan bordering Tajikistan.

--
Sona Bari
External Relations
Polio Eradication Initiative
World Health Organization
20 Avenue Appia,
CH-1211 Geneva 27, Switzerland
